<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="461" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1276,2021]" pageId="10" pageNumber="461">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1636,1661]" pageId="10" pageNumber="461">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Within the genus, 
<taxonomicName authority="Desutter-Grandcolas" authorityName="Desutter-Grandcolas" box="[535,999,1636,1661]" class="Insecta" family="Phalangopsidae" genus="Afrophaloria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="461" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amani" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[535,758,1636,1661]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="461">Afrophaloria amani</emphasis>
Desutter-Grandcolas
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1011,1072,1637,1660]" pageId="10" pageNumber="461" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be identified by its massive pronotum, the ivory coloration of supra anal plate, tergites and cerci base in males (yellowish brown and not as contrasted in females), and its male and female genitalia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="462" pageId="10" pageNumber="461" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1276,2021]" box="[151,297,1743,1768]" pageId="10" pageNumber="461">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1743,1768]" pageId="10" pageNumber="461">Description.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1276,2021]" box="[199,830,1780,1805]" pageId="10" pageNumber="461">In addition to the characters of the subfamily and genus:</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1276,2021]" lastBlockId="11.[151,1437,151,1184]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="462" pageId="10" pageNumber="461">
Joint 
<number box="[260,274,1816,1840]" pageId="10" pageNumber="461" value="4.0">4</number>
of maxillary palpi slightly longer than joint 
<number box="[776,790,1816,1840]" pageId="10" pageNumber="461" value="3.0">3</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[805,872,1815,1840]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[150,1433,202,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[150,1436,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 2. Afrophaloria Desutter-Grandcolas, n. gen. Maxillary palpi (A – D), Male subgenital plate, lateral (E, G, I) and ventral (F, H), Female subgenital plate, ventral (J – M), Female copulatory papilla (N – R) in: Afrophaloria amani Desutter- Grandcolas, n. sp. (A male, B female, E, F, N), Afrophaloria hempae Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp. (C, G, H, K, O) and Afrophaloria apiariensis Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp. (D, I, L, M, P dorsal, Q ventral, R lateral). Scale bars 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241859/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="461">
Fig. 
<number box="[858,872,1816,1840]" pageId="10" pageNumber="461" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
A, B). DD only slightly wider than long, posterior margin convex (
<figureCitation box="[337,402,1852,1877]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1801,1823]" captionTargetBox="[199,1397,196,1745]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[196,1401,196,1745]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 1. Afrophaloria amani Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp., male holotype, habitus (A), head and pronotum, dorsal (B), supra anal plate (D) and subgenital plate (E); male paratype MNHN-EO-ENSIF 3697, head, lateral (C); female allotype, habitus dorsal (F), habitus lateral (G), face (H), supra anal plate (I), subgenital plate (J). Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241858/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="461">
Fig. 
<number box="[391,402,1852,1876]" pageId="10" pageNumber="461" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A, F). 
<collectionCode box="[483,528,1853,1876]" pageId="10" pageNumber="461">TIII</collectionCode>
without serrulation between apical and subapical spurs, and between subapical spurs (one examined female with one spine between outer subapical spurs 
<number box="[1003,1017,1888,1912]" pageId="10" pageNumber="461" value="3.0">3</number>
and 
<number box="[1075,1092,1888,1912]" pageId="10" pageNumber="461" value="4.0">4</number>
); above subapical spurs, outer spines: five to eight (mean six) in males, five to eight (mean 6,4) in females; inner spines: one to four (mean 
<number box="[1383,1397,1924,1948]" pageId="10" pageNumber="461" value="3.0">3</number>
) in males, zero to three (mean 1,9) in females. Basitarsomeres III quite long for the genus (
<figureCitation box="[1139,1202,1960,1985]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1801,1823]" captionTargetBox="[199,1397,196,1745]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[196,1401,196,1745]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 1. Afrophaloria amani Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp., male holotype, habitus (A), head and pronotum, dorsal (B), supra anal plate (D) and subgenital plate (E); male paratype MNHN-EO-ENSIF 3697, head, lateral (C); female allotype, habitus dorsal (F), habitus lateral (G), face (H), supra anal plate (I), subgenital plate (J). Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241858/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="461">
Fig. 
<number box="[1192,1202,1960,1984]" pageId="10" pageNumber="461" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A, F, G), the longest inner apical spur reaching about three fourth of basitarsomere length; serrrulation: no inner spine in addition to apical one (one examined male with one additional inner spine); outer spines: three to five (mean 3,8) in males, one to four (mean three) in females
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,1184]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,223,248]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Coloration.</emphasis>
Head dorsum brown, with four indistinct darker lines (behind each lateral ocellus and from the anterior angle of each eye: 
<figureCitation box="[471,537,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1801,1823]" captionTargetBox="[199,1397,196,1745]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[196,1401,196,1745]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 1. Afrophaloria amani Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp., male holotype, habitus (A), head and pronotum, dorsal (B), supra anal plate (D) and subgenital plate (E); male paratype MNHN-EO-ENSIF 3697, head, lateral (C); female allotype, habitus dorsal (F), habitus lateral (G), face (H), supra anal plate (I), subgenital plate (J). Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241858/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
Fig. 
<number box="[526,537,260,284]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
F); ocelli ivory, a black spot behind the median ocellus (
<figureCitation box="[1203,1270,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1801,1823]" captionTargetBox="[199,1397,196,1745]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[196,1401,196,1745]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 1. Afrophaloria amani Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp., male holotype, habitus (A), head and pronotum, dorsal (B), supra anal plate (D) and subgenital plate (E); male paratype MNHN-EO-ENSIF 3697, head, lateral (C); female allotype, habitus dorsal (F), habitus lateral (G), face (H), supra anal plate (I), subgenital plate (J). Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241858/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
Fig. 
<number box="[1259,1270,260,284]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B, C). Cheeks brown dorsally, yellowish along the eye, along their posterior margin, and in their lower half (
<figureCitation box="[1223,1288,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1801,1823]" captionTargetBox="[199,1397,196,1745]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[196,1401,196,1745]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 1. Afrophaloria amani Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp., male holotype, habitus (A), head and pronotum, dorsal (B), supra anal plate (D) and subgenital plate (E); male paratype MNHN-EO-ENSIF 3697, head, lateral (C); female allotype, habitus dorsal (F), habitus lateral (G), face (H), supra anal plate (I), subgenital plate (J). Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241858/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
Fig. 
<number box="[1277,1288,296,320]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C). Face and mouthparts yellowish with indistinct brown pattern (
<figureCitation box="[749,814,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1801,1823]" captionTargetBox="[199,1397,196,1745]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[196,1401,196,1745]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 1. Afrophaloria amani Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp., male holotype, habitus (A), head and pronotum, dorsal (B), supra anal plate (D) and subgenital plate (E); male paratype MNHN-EO-ENSIF 3697, head, lateral (C); female allotype, habitus dorsal (F), habitus lateral (G), face (H), supra anal plate (I), subgenital plate (J). Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241858/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
Fig. 
<number box="[803,814,332,356]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
H). Maxillary palpi (
<figureCitation box="[1054,1119,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1801,1823]" captionTargetBox="[199,1397,196,1745]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[196,1401,196,1745]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 1. Afrophaloria amani Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp., male holotype, habitus (A), head and pronotum, dorsal (B), supra anal plate (D) and subgenital plate (E); male paratype MNHN-EO-ENSIF 3697, head, lateral (C); female allotype, habitus dorsal (F), habitus lateral (G), face (H), supra anal plate (I), subgenital plate (J). Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241858/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
Fig. 
<number box="[1108,1119,332,356]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C), scapes (
<figureCitation box="[1255,1320,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1801,1823]" captionTargetBox="[199,1397,196,1745]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[196,1401,196,1745]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 1. Afrophaloria amani Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp., male holotype, habitus (A), head and pronotum, dorsal (B), supra anal plate (D) and subgenital plate (E); male paratype MNHN-EO-ENSIF 3697, head, lateral (C); female allotype, habitus dorsal (F), habitus lateral (G), face (H), supra anal plate (I), subgenital plate (J). Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241858/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
Fig. 
<number box="[1309,1320,332,356]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B, H) and antennae (
<figureCitation box="[265,327,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1801,1823]" captionTargetBox="[199,1397,196,1745]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[196,1401,196,1745]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 1. Afrophaloria amani Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp., male holotype, habitus (A), head and pronotum, dorsal (B), supra anal plate (D) and subgenital plate (E); male paratype MNHN-EO-ENSIF 3697, head, lateral (C); female allotype, habitus dorsal (F), habitus lateral (G), face (H), supra anal plate (I), subgenital plate (J). Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241858/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
Fig. 
<number box="[317,327,368,392]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A, F) yellowish, some lighter articles along the antennae, without a distinct color pattern. Pronotum dark brown, including the margins (
<figureCitation box="[564,630,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1801,1823]" captionTargetBox="[199,1397,196,1745]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[196,1401,196,1745]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 1. Afrophaloria amani Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp., male holotype, habitus (A), head and pronotum, dorsal (B), supra anal plate (D) and subgenital plate (E); male paratype MNHN-EO-ENSIF 3697, head, lateral (C); female allotype, habitus dorsal (F), habitus lateral (G), face (H), supra anal plate (I), subgenital plate (J). Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241858/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
Fig. 
<number box="[619,630,404,428]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B); dorsal muscular inscriptions, parts of the dorsal disc and a spot in lateral anterior angle marked with yellowish, 
<figureCitation box="[656,718,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1801,1823]" captionTargetBox="[199,1397,196,1745]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[196,1401,196,1745]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 1. Afrophaloria amani Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp., male holotype, habitus (A), head and pronotum, dorsal (B), supra anal plate (D) and subgenital plate (E); male paratype MNHN-EO-ENSIF 3697, head, lateral (C); female allotype, habitus dorsal (F), habitus lateral (G), face (H), supra anal plate (I), subgenital plate (J). Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241858/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
Fig. 
<number box="[707,718,440,464]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B, C, G). Legs yellowish with some brownish patterns, with few brown spots at setae bases (
<figureCitation box="[458,520,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1801,1823]" captionTargetBox="[199,1397,196,1745]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[196,1401,196,1745]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 1. Afrophaloria amani Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp., male holotype, habitus (A), head and pronotum, dorsal (B), supra anal plate (D) and subgenital plate (E); male paratype MNHN-EO-ENSIF 3697, head, lateral (C); female allotype, habitus dorsal (F), habitus lateral (G), face (H), supra anal plate (I), subgenital plate (J). Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241858/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
Fig. 
<number box="[510,520,476,500]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A, F, G): FI, FII with a faint distal ring, and a hardly distinct subdistal one; TI, TII somewhat darker, with four undistinct rings; 
<collectionCode box="[670,713,512,535]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">FIII</collectionCode>
with undistinct distal ring and oblique lines; 
<collectionCode box="[1242,1287,512,535]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">TIII</collectionCode>
light brown, lighter at base; tarsomeres yellowish, with a short brown ring basally and a longer one apically; 
<collectionCode box="[1244,1289,549,572]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">TIII</collectionCode>
spurs brown on their basal half length, then yellowish with black apex. Tergites dark brown to black brown, the supra anal plate, sternites and subgenital plate lighter (see infra). Cerci dark brown with a light basal ring.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,1184]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,267,655,680]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Male.</emphasis>
Posterior margin of metanotum and tergites 
<number box="[765,807,656,680]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4</number>
somewhat lighter (
<figureCitation box="[1022,1084,655,680]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1801,1823]" captionTargetBox="[199,1397,196,1745]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[196,1401,196,1745]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 1. Afrophaloria amani Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp., male holotype, habitus (A), head and pronotum, dorsal (B), supra anal plate (D) and subgenital plate (E); male paratype MNHN-EO-ENSIF 3697, head, lateral (C); female allotype, habitus dorsal (F), habitus lateral (G), face (H), supra anal plate (I), subgenital plate (J). Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241858/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
Fig. 
<number box="[1073,1084,656,680]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Supra anal plate wider than long, its distal part not particularly elongate; ivory, the median furrow and lateral spots light brown (
<figureCitation box="[1296,1360,692,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1801,1823]" captionTargetBox="[199,1397,196,1745]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[196,1401,196,1745]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 1. Afrophaloria amani Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp., male holotype, habitus (A), head and pronotum, dorsal (B), supra anal plate (D) and subgenital plate (E); male paratype MNHN-EO-ENSIF 3697, head, lateral (C); female allotype, habitus dorsal (F), habitus lateral (G), face (H), supra anal plate (I), subgenital plate (J). Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241858/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
Fig. 
<number box="[1350,1360,692,716]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A, D). Subgenital plate short and not very low, distal margin straigth (
<figureCitation box="[856,923,727,752]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1801,1823]" captionTargetBox="[199,1397,196,1745]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[196,1401,196,1745]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 1. Afrophaloria amani Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp., male holotype, habitus (A), head and pronotum, dorsal (B), supra anal plate (D) and subgenital plate (E); male paratype MNHN-EO-ENSIF 3697, head, lateral (C); female allotype, habitus dorsal (F), habitus lateral (G), face (H), supra anal plate (I), subgenital plate (J). Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241858/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
Figs 
<number box="[912,923,728,752]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
E, 
<number box="[957,972,728,752]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" value="2.0">2</number>
E, F).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,1184]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,379,764,789]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
<figureCitation box="[388,454,764,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,195,1916]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[169,1417,193,1931]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 3. Afrophaloria Desutter-Grandcolas, n. gen. Male genitalia, dorsal (A, D, G), ventral (B, E, H), lateral (C, F, I) in: Afrophaloria amani Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp. (A – C), Afrophaloria hempae Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp. (D – F) and Afrophaloria apiariensis Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp. (G – I). Abbreviations: see page 3." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241860/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
Fig. 
<number box="[442,454,764,788]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
A–C. Upper part of pseudepiphallus narrow and thick. Pseudepiphallus membranous, except for a pair of lateral sclerites prolonged as thick hooks directed ventrally, these hooks not very long (
<figureCitation box="[1335,1401,799,824]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,195,1916]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[169,1417,193,1931]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 3. Afrophaloria Desutter-Grandcolas, n. gen. Male genitalia, dorsal (A, D, G), ventral (B, E, H), lateral (C, F, I) in: Afrophaloria amani Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp. (A – C), Afrophaloria hempae Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp. (D – F) and Afrophaloria apiariensis Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp. (G – I). Abbreviations: see page 3." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241860/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
Fig. 
<number box="[1387,1401,800,824]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
C), not going beyond the ectophallic fold; rami long and narrow, slightly curved; pseudepiphallic parameres very long, hardly sclerotized. Ectophallic apodemes short, curved (
<figureCitation box="[811,882,871,896]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,195,1916]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[169,1417,193,1931]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 3. Afrophaloria Desutter-Grandcolas, n. gen. Male genitalia, dorsal (A, D, G), ventral (B, E, H), lateral (C, F, I) in: Afrophaloria amani Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp. (A – C), Afrophaloria hempae Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp. (D – F) and Afrophaloria apiariensis Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp. (G – I). Abbreviations: see page 3." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241860/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
Fig. 
<number box="[869,882,872,896]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
A, B); dorsal and ventral sclerotization of epiectophallic invagination connected by the arc: (
<figureCitation box="[737,813,908,933]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,195,1916]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[169,1417,193,1931]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 3. Afrophaloria Desutter-Grandcolas, n. gen. Male genitalia, dorsal (A, D, G), ventral (B, E, H), lateral (C, F, I) in: Afrophaloria amani Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp. (A – C), Afrophaloria hempae Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp. (D – F) and Afrophaloria apiariensis Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp. (G – I). Abbreviations: see page 3." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241860/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
Fig. 
<number box="[799,813,908,932]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Ectophallic fold very long, going well beyond pseudepiphallic hooks; sclerotized; apex widely split, asymmetrical, the left lobe (in dorsal view: 
<figureCitation box="[1266,1332,943,968]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,195,1916]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[169,1417,193,1931]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 3. Afrophaloria Desutter-Grandcolas, n. gen. Male genitalia, dorsal (A, D, G), ventral (B, E, H), lateral (C, F, I) in: Afrophaloria amani Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp. (A – C), Afrophaloria hempae Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp. (D – F) and Afrophaloria apiariensis Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp. (G – I). Abbreviations: see page 3." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241860/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
Fig. 
<number box="[1319,1332,944,968]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
A) larger than the right lobe. Endophallic sclerite squared, prolonged distally on the ventral side of ectophallic fold (
<figureCitation box="[1335,1400,980,1005]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,195,1916]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[169,1417,193,1931]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 3. Afrophaloria Desutter-Grandcolas, n. gen. Male genitalia, dorsal (A, D, G), ventral (B, E, H), lateral (C, F, I) in: Afrophaloria amani Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp. (A – C), Afrophaloria hempae Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp. (D – F) and Afrophaloria apiariensis Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp. (G – I). Abbreviations: see page 3." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241860/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
Fig. 
<number box="[1386,1400,980,1004]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
B); endophallic apodemes and dorsal ectophallic valves very short.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,1184]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,1052,1077]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Female.</emphasis>
Coloration of abdomen often less regularly dark brown than in males (
<figureCitation box="[1110,1174,1052,1077]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1801,1823]" captionTargetBox="[199,1397,196,1745]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[196,1401,196,1745]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 1. Afrophaloria amani Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp., male holotype, habitus (A), head and pronotum, dorsal (B), supra anal plate (D) and subgenital plate (E); male paratype MNHN-EO-ENSIF 3697, head, lateral (C); female allotype, habitus dorsal (F), habitus lateral (G), face (H), supra anal plate (I), subgenital plate (J). Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241858/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
Fig. 
<number box="[1164,1174,1052,1076]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
F, G). Subgenital plate wider than long; apex deeply bisinuate (
<figureCitation box="[599,668,1087,1112]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[150,1433,202,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[150,1436,193,1890]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 2. Afrophaloria Desutter-Grandcolas, n. gen. Maxillary palpi (A – D), Male subgenital plate, lateral (E, G, I) and ventral (F, H), Female subgenital plate, ventral (J – M), Female copulatory papilla (N – R) in: Afrophaloria amani Desutter- Grandcolas, n. sp. (A male, B female, E, F, N), Afrophaloria hempae Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp. (C, G, H, K, O) and Afrophaloria apiariensis Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp. (D, I, L, M, P dorsal, Q ventral, R lateral). Scale bars 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241859/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
Fig. 
<number box="[652,668,1088,1112]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
J). Ovipositor shorter than 
<collectionCode box="[967,1016,1088,1111]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">TIII</collectionCode>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,1184]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,405,1124,1149]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
<figureCitation box="[413,478,1124,1149]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1801,1823]" captionTargetBox="[199,1397,196,1745]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[196,1401,196,1745]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 1. Afrophaloria amani Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp., male holotype, habitus (A), head and pronotum, dorsal (B), supra anal plate (D) and subgenital plate (E); male paratype MNHN-EO-ENSIF 3697, head, lateral (C); female allotype, habitus dorsal (F), habitus lateral (G), face (H), supra anal plate (I), subgenital plate (J). Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241858/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
Fig. 
<number box="[467,478,1124,1148]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" value="1.0">
<specimenCount box="[467,478,1124,1148]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" type="generic">1</specimenCount>
</number>
</figureCitation>
N. Copulatory papilla having the shape of a thin, half ring; spermathecal duct thick and short. Spermatheca thin and elongate.
</paragraph>
